<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920311-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>920311-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Cirrus Logic Inc.:   Firm Reaches Pact to Buy   Closely Held Chip Maker</HL><DATE>03/11/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5</SO><CO>   CRUS WNEWS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BUYBACKS (BBK)PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS (PER)ACQUISITIONS, MERGERS, TAKEOVERS (TNM)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Cirrus Logic Inc., Fremont, Calif., said it agreed toacquire Acumos Inc., a closely held Foster City, Calif.,computer chip maker, for stock valued at $67 million.   Cirrus, which sells chips in many markets, said it willissue 3.6 million shares of its common stock in exchange forall the outstanding shares of Acumos. Cirrus closed at$18.675, unchanged, in national over-the-counter tradingyesterday. Cirrus said it won't assume any new debt under theagreement, which is subject to approval by Acumos'sshareholders.</LP><TEXT>   Acumos sells chips that control the displays in desktoppersonal computers, complementing Cirrus's strength incontrol chips for lap-top and notebook PCs, Cirrus said.Under the agreement, Acumos's products and employees will bemerged into Cirrus. Doug Bartek, president and chiefexecutive of Acumos, will become a Cirrus vice president,Cirrus said.</TEXT></DOC>